Q

Query - Class in com.logquerier
Represents the query object, it has fields such as startHour, endHour etc The data in this object uses helper functions to extract hours, minutes etc This query object will be created by the main class and will be passed onto the LogQuerie class
Query(String) - Constructor for class com.logquerier.Query
Constructor method to store query string as an object.
QueryCpuUsage - Class in com.logquerier
Represents the main class for querying the CPU usage
QueryCpuUsage() - Constructor for class com.logquerier.QueryCpuUsage
 
QueryFormatVerifier - Class in com.logquerier.utilities
This class checks the query string if it adheres to the following format QUERY IP_ADDRESS CPU_ID START_DATE START_HOUR:START_MIN END_DATE END_HOUR:END_MIN in the question, it parses through each of the query parameters and throws a WrongQueryFormatException in case the query string fails to stick to the format
QueryFormatVerifier() - Constructor for class com.logquerier.utilities.QueryFormatVerifier
